==Documentation==
This template creates a full DLC page layout with hero section, tabs, wiki content, and sidebar.
Uses Semantic MediaWiki for structured data storage and display.

DLC (Downloadable Content) represents add-ons, expansions, and downloadable content for games.

===Parameters===
{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Parameter !! Description
|-
|| Name || Display name of the DLC
|-
|| Guid || Giant Bomb API identifier
|-
|| Aliases || Alternative names (comma-separated)
|-
|| Image || DLC image filename
|-
|| BackgroundImage || Background image filename
|-
|| Deck || Short description shown in hero
|-
|| Game || The base game this DLC is for
|-
|| Platform || Platform this DLC is available on
|-
|| ReleaseDateType || Release date type (None, Full, Month, Quarter, Year)
|-
|| ReleaseDate || Release date of the DLC
|-
|| MonthPart || Month part of a monthly release date (not saved to smw)
|-
|| MonthYearPart || Year part of a monthly release date (not saved to smw)
|-
|| QuarterPart ||  Quarter part of a quarterly release date (not saved to smw)
|-
|| QuarterYearPart || Year part of quarterly release date (not saved to smw)
|-
|| YearPart || Year part of a yearly release date (not saved to smw)
|-
|| LaunchPrice || Original price at launch
|}

===Usage===
<pre>
{{DLC
| Name = The Witcher 3: Blood and Wine
| Guid = 3020-1234
| Deck = A massive expansion to The Witcher 3...
| Game = Games/The_Witcher_3
| Platform = Platforms/PC
| ReleaseDateType = Full
| ReleaseDate = 2016-05-31
| LaunchPrice = $19.99
}}

== Overview ==
Your wiki content here...

{{DLCEnd}}
</pre>
